  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Applicable regulatory requirement is FDA guidance on computational modeling (2016) and ASME V&V 40-2018; a structured Requirement object capturing these obligations is documented in the package body under the requirements node, though no top-level bindsRequirement link is emitted under the Minimal profile binding rules.",
